# T14-lid-closed — laptop lid CLOSED, external HDMI monitor only.
# autorandr matches profiles by EDID (the 'setup' file), so this profile
# cannot be fabricated: it must be saved on the T14 with the monitor plugged
# and the laptop panel off. autorandr ignores this file (only 'config',
# 'setup', and hook scripts matter), so it is safe to leave as a reminder.
#
# Layout (from the old bin/monitors-config): HDMI primary, laptop panel off.
#
# 1. Plug the monitor, then set the layout (eDP off simulates lid closed):
#      xrandr --output HDMI-1 --primary --auto --output eDP-1 --off
#
# 2. Capture it:
#      autorandr --save T14-lid-closed
#
# 3. Copy the saved profile back into the repo:
#      cp -r ~/.config/autorandr/T14-lid-closed ~/environment/dotfiles/config/.config/autorandr/
#
# 4. Commit.
